# Backend Rules

## Stack
- Fastify v5 + TypeScript
- @fastify/websocket for WebSocket support
- Drizzle ORM + postgres (node-postgres driver)
- better-auth for JWT authentication
- Runs as separate process on port 3001 (Next.js runs on 3000)

## Database Schema (PostgreSQL)
Tables:
- organizations (id, name, slug, created_at)
- users (id, org_id, name, email, avatar_url, role, created_at)
- projects (id, org_id, name, color, status, owner_id, start_date, end_date, created_at)
- phases (id, project_id, name, order_index, entry_conditions jsonb)
- tasks (id, phase_id, title, description, status, priority, effort_estimate, due_date, canvas_x float, canvas_y float, is_critical_path bool, slack_time int, created_at, updated_at)
- task_assignments (task_id, user_id) — many-to-many
- task_dependencies (upstream_task_id, downstream_task_id, type) — type: FS|FF|SS
- comments (id, task_id, user_id, content, created_at)
- canvas_bookmarks (id, user_id, name, viewport_x, viewport_y, viewport_zoom)

## WebSocket Events
All WS messages follow: { type: string, payload: any, orgId: string, userId: string }

Inbound (client → server):
- TASK_UPDATE: { taskId, changes }
- TASK_CREATE: { phaseId, data }
- DEPENDENCY_ADD: { upstreamId, downstreamId, depType }
- DEPENDENCY_REMOVE: { upstreamId, downstreamId }
- CANVAS_MOVE: { nodeId, x, y } — debounced, 500ms
- CURSOR_MOVE: { x, y } — presence only, not persisted

Outbound (server → all org clients):
- TASK_UPDATED: broadcast after DB write + CPM recompute
- CPM_RESULT: { criticalPath: string[], taskFloats: Record<string, number> }
- PRESENCE_UPDATE: { userId, cursor: {x,y}, activeNodeId }
- WORKLOAD_UPDATE: { userId, loadPercent, taskCount }

## CPM Server-Side
- server/graph/cpm.ts runs topological sort on task dependency graph
- Triggered after any TASK_UPDATE or DEPENDENCY_ADD/REMOVE event
- Result broadcast to all connected org clients via CPM_RESULT event
- Max recompute time target: < 50ms for up to 500 tasks

## REST Endpoints
- GET /api/org/:orgId/graph — returns full project/phase/task graph for canvas hydration
- GET /api/org/:orgId/workload — returns person workload aggregation
- POST /api/tasks — create task
- PATCH /api/tasks/:id — update task
- POST /api/dependencies — add dependency
- DELETE /api/dependencies — remove dependency
- GET /api/projects/:id/critical-path — returns current critical path
